# WHAT IT IS
#   Keel is "a fast, statically-typed interpreted language
#   that aims to combine Rust-like syntax with Python's
#   ease-of-use".  Goal:  a faster alternative to Python that
#   sits closer to low-level languages while remaining
#   accessible.
#
#   Headline features:
#     • Fast — ~2-10× faster than Python on the upstream
#       benchmark suite (see `docs/BENCHMARKS.md`), driven
#       by aggressive compile-time optimizations
#     • Familiar Rust-like syntax with Python ergonomics
#     • Statically typed with **zero annotations**: full
#       type inference, static type checking, polymorphism
#     • FFI support: call C / dynamic libraries directly
#       from Keel
#     • Built-in REPL  (invoke `keel` with no args)
#     • Near-future roadmap: structs, higher-order
#       functions, embedding API with limits
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from README "Usage"
